20.41	Steve_Furber	Steve Furber	Professor Stephen Byram Furber CBE, FRS, FREng (born 1953 in Manchester, England) is the ICL Professor of Computer Engineering at the School of Computer Science at the University of Manchester but is probably best known for his work at Acorn where he was one of the designers of the BBC Micro and the ARM 32-bit RISC microprocessor.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Steve_Furber.jpg/200px-Steve_Furber.jpg
